Well, I'll see how it goes.  Need to test and see if nullifying makes pet lose levels, that would be doom for beastlords.<br>
<br>
Toxiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/01 1:10:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.phata1.com/images/pope1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beastlords and pvp</span><hr size=1> Last i read they have no form of movement reduction(root, snare, etc..)<br>
If this is still true, i'd imagine they will be one of the worst pvp classes out there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uquiggleyvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quiggley VZ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/01 7:55:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://strike9.com/eq/Quiggley/fullsize/the_lina_chevee.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beastlords and pvp</span><hr size=1> this is the one class i forsee that bards will own.. heh <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uquiggleyvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quiggley VZ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/12/01 3:38:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukevtheif.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KevTheif</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/01 6:40:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> it will come down to how good the beastlord epic is. mages own with their epic. if beast lords get a epic pet then they will own too becuase they get a good pet and wont die in 3 melee hits <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utoxiss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toxiss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 2:44:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> A friend of mine who is a beastlord also, tells me that the pet level buff cannot be nullified, so that's a huge bonus.  Pet would be completely useless if it could.  And yes, bards will own us, but they are a pain for just about everyone if they know what they are doing.<br>
