Toxiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ustalken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stalken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 5:23:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> Grahl,<br>
<br>
Yeah I remember you. You ready to join Angerthas yet =)<br>
<br>
The population of cats is slowly starting to rise now. Which is good. We can pretty much level to 20 in safety kind of like Iksar in FoB. So that's definitely a good thing.<br>
<br>
I took my druid into the Grimling Forest a couple days ago and almost got raped. I zoned in and there were like 4 or 5 reds sitting there. I start back pedaling and zone with them in hot pursuit. I zone fast. Beat them by 30 seconds so I was able to camp out. Imagine they were no too happy =)<br>
<br>
I think they were the exception though and not the norm for that zone. Other than that one incident it has been real quiet. Almost never see anyone in the Caverns cept maybe a couple of kitties taking out the giant mushroom guys.<br>
<br>
Hollowshade comes and goes. There have been neuts there a handful of times, but like I said I think they are just exploring and won't be staying for the long haul.<br>
<br>
I've gotten Stalken to 18 in the Thicket pretty easily. That camp directly up the road from the town is awesome. I stayed there from 12th-18th. The camp switches from Gor Taku to Shak Dratha (which are higher level) almost every other spawn cycle.<br>
<br>
Having trouble finding a group now since most of the other cats are below 10th still. So I'm moving to EF for a couple levels and see how that goes.<br>
<br>
Anyway I'll see ya in game man<br>
<br>
